&lt;p&gt;&amp;mdash; Penn Jillette&lt;/p&gt;</content><category term="quote"></category><category term="quote"></category></entry><entry><title>Quote</title><link href="https://dimitris.glezos.com/weblog/2013/09/01/the-longest-journey-is-the-journey-inward-for-he/" rel="alternate"></link><published>2013-09-01T04:24:21+00:00</published><updated>2013-09-01T04:24:21+00:00</updated><author><name>glezos-blog</name></author><id>tag:dimitris.glezos.com,2013-09-01:/weblog/2013/09/01/the-longest-journey-is-the-journey-inward-for-he/</id><content type="html">&lt;p&gt;The longest journey is the journey inward, for he who has chosen his destiny has started upon his quest for the source of his being.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;mdash; Dag Hammarskjöld&lt;/p&gt;</content><category term="quote"></category><category term="quote"></category></entry><entry><title>Quote</title><link href="https://dimitris.glezos.com/weblog/2013/07/02/all-i-want-more-than-anything-is-to-work-with/" rel="alternate"></link><published>2013-07-02T08:08:09+00:00</published><updated>2013-07-02T08:08:09+00:00</updated><author><name>glezos-blog</name></author><id>tag:dimitris.glezos.com,2013-07-02:/weblog/2013/07/02/all-i-want-more-than-anything-is-to-work-with/</id><content type="html">&lt;p&gt;All I want more than anything is to work with people who give a fuck as much as I do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;mdash; Marcus '&lt;a href="https://twitter.com/djWHEAT"&gt;djWHEAT&lt;/a&gt;' Graham&lt;/p&gt;</content><category term="quote"></category><category term="quote"></category></entry><entry><title>Photo</title><link href="https://dimitris.glezos.com/weblog/2012/12/02/skiing-at-lake-tahoe-in-the-sierras/" rel="alternate"></link><published>2012-12-02T03:47:39+00:00</published><updated>2012-12-02T03:47:39+00:00</updated><author><name>glezos-blog</name></author><id>tag:dimitris.glezos.com,2012-12-02:/weblog/2012/12/02/skiing-at-lake-tahoe-in-the-sierras/</id><content type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="image0" src="https://64.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_medx7ffw9f1qaawg5o1_1280.jpg"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content><category term="photo"></category><category term="photo"></category></entry><entry><title>Photo</title><link href="https://dimitris.glezos.com/weblog/2012/11/24/home-made-thai-red-curry-taste-wise-a-worthy/" rel="alternate"></link><published>2012-11-24T23:13:17+00:00</published><updated>2012-11-24T23:13:17+00:00</updated><author><name>glezos-blog</name></author><id>tag:dimitris.glezos.com,2012-11-24:/weblog/2012/11/24/home-made-thai-red-curry-taste-wise-a-worthy/</id><content type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="image0" src="https://64.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_me0lu5fRyD1qaawg5o1_1280.jpg"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content><category term="photo"></category><category term="photo"></category></entry><entry><title>Quote</title><link href="https://dimitris.glezos.com/weblog/2012/09/08/the-pines-were-roaring-on-the-height-the-winds/" rel="alternate"></link><published>2012-09-08T19:14:52+00:00</published><updated>2012-09-08T19:14:52+00:00</updated><author><name>glezos-blog</name></author><id>tag:dimitris.glezos.com,2012-09-08:/weblog/2012/09/08/the-pines-were-roaring-on-the-height-the-winds/</id><content type="html">&lt;p&gt;The pines were roaring on the height.. The winds were moaning in the night.. The trees like torches blazed with light..&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;mdash; The Hobbit&lt;/p&gt;</content><category term="quote"></category><category term="quote"></category></entry><entry><title>Quote</title><link href="https://dimitris.glezos.com/weblog/2012/07/17/the-most-important-piece-of-advice-i-can-give-you/" rel="alternate"></link><published>2012-07-17T00:34:07+00:00</published><updated>2012-07-17T00:34:07+00:00</updated><author><name>glezos-blog</name></author><id>tag:dimitris.glezos.com,2012-07-17:/weblog/2012/07/17/the-most-important-piece-of-advice-i-can-give-you/</id><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;The most important piece of advice I can give you on the path to happiness, is not just be yourself, but be your weird self. It takes too much energy to be other than your weird self. We spend so much of our lives living up to the expectations of …&lt;/p&gt;</summary><content type="html">&lt;p&gt;The most important piece of advice I can give you on the path to happiness, is not just be yourself, but be your weird self. It takes too much energy to be other than your weird self. We spend so much of our lives living up to the expectations of others.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It’s our collection of screw ups, stories and idiosyncrasies, that make us weird and interesting. Weirdness is why we adore our friends. Weirdness is what binds us to our colleagues. Weirdness is what sets us apart and gets us hired. Be your unapologetic weird selves.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;mdash; &lt;a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RskzYHPlh5U"&gt;Chris Sacca&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;a href="http://blog.alexmaccaw.com/heres-to-the-misfits"&gt;via&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;</content><category term="quote"></category><category term="quote"></category></entry><entry><title>Quote</title><link href="https://dimitris.glezos.com/weblog/2012/07/02/i-believe-that-love-that-is-true-and-real-creates/" rel="alternate"></link><published>2012-07-02T06:19:46+00:00</published><updated>2012-07-02T06:19:46+00:00</updated><author><name>glezos-blog</name></author><id>tag:dimitris.glezos.com,2012-07-02:/weblog/2012/07/02/i-believe-that-love-that-is-true-and-real-creates/</id><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;I believe that love that is true and real creates a respite from death. All cowardice comes from not loving or not loving well, which is the same thing. And when the man who is brave and true looks death squarely in the face like some rhino hunters I know …&lt;/p&gt;</summary><content type="html">&lt;p&gt;I believe that love that is true and real creates a respite from death. All cowardice comes from not loving or not loving well, which is the same thing. And when the man who is brave and true looks death squarely in the face like some rhino hunters I know or Belmonte, who is truly brave, it is because they love with sufficient passion to push death out of their minds. Until it returns, as it does to all men. And then you must make really good love again.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;mdash; Ernest Hemingway from Woody Allen's "Midnight in Paris"&lt;/p&gt;</content><category term="quote"></category><category term="quote"></category></entry></feed>